ABUJA – Abuja-based human rights activist, Deji Adeyanju has commended President Muhammadu Buhari for not interfering with the ongoing drug deal case of suspended Deputy Commissioner of Police, DCP, Abba Kyari. In a tweet on Tuesday, Adeyanju wrote: “I commend President Buhari and his government for not interfering with this Abba Kyari cocaine trafficking issue.” Kyari, a former head of the Police Intelligence Response Team, IRT, has found himself in fresh trouble with  National Drugs Law Enforcement Agency ( NDLEA, ) who indicted him of selling drugs. 2023: Group Canvasses Tinubu As Consensus Candidates Of All… FCT Council Polls: Legal Practitioner Hails Aliyu For Enhancing… The NDLEA had declared him wanted after evidence linked him to a drug cartel operating along the Brazil-Ethiopia-Nigeria route. After declaring him wanted, the agency released video evidence of Kyari attempting to bribe an NDLEA operative.